00:17:07,540 --> 00:17:11,250
would I be able to do stuff
that even you can't do, Kyubey?

267
00:17:11,630 --> 00:17:12,370
Like what?

268
00:17:12,580 --> 00:17:15,000
Like if I went ahead and made a contract with you,

269
00:17:15,220 --> 00:17:17,190
could I turn Sayaka back to normal?

270
00:17:17,650 --> 00:17:19,470
That would be like child's play for you.

271
00:17:19,810 --> 00:17:22,640
Would that be worth trading your soul for?

272
00:17:23,290 --> 00:17:24,250
Would you like to?

273
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:25,270
Yes.

274
00:17:25,430 --> 00:17:26,470
For Sayaka, I would.

275
00:17:26,870 --> 00:17:27,800
I'll do it.

276
00:17:28,080 --> 00:17:29,260
I wanna be...

277
00:17:29,720 --> 00:17:30,900
a magical...

278
00:17:35,730 --> 00:17:36,720
Uh..?!

279
00:17:48,160 --> 00:17:49,700
What did you do?

280
00:17:49,940 --> 00:17:51,410
You didn't have to kill him!

281
00:17:51,790 --> 00:17:52,860
You idiot.

282
00:17:53,310 --> 00:17:54,550
Why do you do that?

283
00:17:54,830 --> 00:17:57,440
Why do you always sacrifice yourself like that?

284
00:17:59,750 --> 00:18:00,600
Huh?

285
00:18:00,960 --> 00:18:03,260
Calling yourself useless, and meaningless...

286
00:18:03,720 --> 00:18:05,930
Stop treating yourself like you don't matter!

287
00:18:06,190 --> 00:18:08,910
Why don't you ever think about
all the people who love you?!

288
00:18:09,280 --> 00:18:10,620
Stop being such a fool!

289
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:13,200
There are so many people who would be sad if you died.

290
00:18:13,450 --> 00:18:15,170
Why can't you understand that?!

291
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:18,130
What about the people who are
trying hard to protect you?!

292
00:18:24,080 --> 00:18:25,120
Homura...

293
00:18:26,650 --> 00:18:27,580
Ah...

294
00:18:28,010 --> 00:18:29,970
I get the feeling we've done this before...

295
00:18:30,950 --> 00:18:32,020
I-Is that true?

296
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:33,800
Have the two of us met before?

297
00:18:34,160 --> 00:18:36,500
I-I can't...

298
00:18:39,590 --> 00:18:40,550
Sorry...

299
00:18:43,840 --> 00:18:45,960
I have to go find Sayaka now.

300
00:18:46,810 --> 00:18:47,770
Wait,

301
00:18:48,340 --> 00:18:50,230
Sayaka Miki is...

302
00:18:50,840 --> 00:18:51,680
I'm sorry.

303
00:18:53,990 --> 00:18:54,970
Wait!

304
00:18:55,780 --> 00:18:56,830
Madoka!

305
00:19:02,920 --> 00:19:05,210
You knew there was no point in doing that.

306
00:19:05,430 --> 00:19:07,070
You don't learn, do you?

307
00:19:08,730 --> 00:19:10,670
I have plenty of spares, you know.

308
00:19:10,940 --> 00:19:13,270
But don't make me use them up for no reason.

309
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:14,640
It's such a waste.

310
00:19:29,610 --> 00:19:32,020
You know, that's the second time you've killed me.

311
00:19:32,470 --> 00:19:35,200
But this time, you showed me what your technique is.

312
00:19:35,500 --> 00:19:38,020
That was time manipulation, wasn't it?

313
00:19:40,780 --> 00:19:41,870
I thought so.

314
00:19:42,300 --> 00:19:44,990
I've suspected for a while,
but I wasn't sure.

315
00:19:45,310 --> 00:19:47,200
You're not from this timeline, are you?

316
00:19:48,860 --> 00:19:52,740
I know what you really are,
and I know what you're planning.

317
00:19:53,010 --> 00:19:54,020
Uh-huh.

318
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:57,120
That's why you've been trying so hard to spoil my plans.

319
00:19:57,480 --> 00:20:00,640
Do you wanna change Madoka Kaname's fate that badly?

320
00:20:00,880 --> 00:20:01,570
I do.

321
00:20:02,510 --> 00:20:04,960
And I'm gonna do whatever it takes to stop you,

322
00:20:05,700 --> 00:20:06,690
Kyubey.

323
00:20:07,920 --> 00:20:09,240
Or should I say,

324
00:20:09,500 --> 00:20:10,970
"Incubator?"

325
00:20:21,260 --> 00:20:22,850
Finally, I found ya.

326
00:20:25,650 --> 00:20:28,730
So how much longer are you gonna
do this stubborn thing, huh?

327
00:20:29,860 --> 00:20:32,910
I'm sorry if I caused you any trouble.

328
00:20:33,220 --> 00:20:34,250
Seriously?

329
00:20:34,690 --> 00:20:36,230
Doesn't sound like you at all.

330
00:20:36,610 --> 00:20:37,720
Hmm...

331
00:20:38,030 --> 00:20:39,090
Yeah, you're right.

332
00:20:39,860 --> 00:20:41,560
I guess I just don't care anymore.

333
00:20:41,980 --> 00:20:44,970
I can't remember...what I thought was so important,

334
00:20:45,300 --> 00:20:47,150
or what was worth protecting, you know.

335
00:20:47,610 --> 00:20:50,640
It's all blank now, doesn't make sense anymore.

336
00:20:51,190 --> 00:20:52,040
Hey, come on.

337
00:20:55,430 --> 00:20:56,250
Ah..!?

338
00:20:56,350 --> 00:20:59,900
Balance means good and bad have
to zero themselves out, right?

339
00:21:00,270 --> 00:21:01,380
That's what you said...

340
00:21:01,800 --> 00:21:03,030
or something like it.

341
00:21:03,690 --> 00:21:05,720
I think I understand what you mean now.

342
00:21:06,870 --> 00:21:10,120
The good thing is,
I did save a few people.

343
00:21:10,810 --> 00:21:12,240
But the bad thing is,

344
00:21:12,610 --> 00:21:13,560
I got angrier,

345
00:21:13,720 --> 00:21:15,770
and my heart filled up with envy and hate.

346
00:21:16,120 --> 00:21:19,010
It got so bad.
I even hurt my best friend.

347
00:21:19,270 --> 00:21:20,010
Sayaka!

348
00:21:20,120 --> 00:21:20,910
Your Soul Gem!

349
00:21:21,360 --> 00:21:26,190
For all the happiness you wish for someone,
someone else gets cursed with equal misery.

350
00:21:26,530 --> 00:21:30,540
That's how it works for magical girls,
and that's how it is for me.

351
00:21:36,420 --> 00:21:37,860
I was stupid...

352
00:21:38,850 --> 00:21:39,940
so stupid.

353
00:22:03,300 --> 00:22:05,720
Sayakaaaa!!

354
00:22:11,130 --> 00:22:15,810
On this planet, you call females who
have yet to become adults "girls."

355
00:22:16,140 --> 00:22:19,790
It makes sense then,
that since you'll eventually become witches,

356
00:22:20,030 --> 00:22:22,720
you should be called "magical girls."

357
00:23:56,130 --> 00:23:58,680
I know this sounds kinda crazy but...

358
00:23:58,970 --> 00:24:02,620
The thing is, we don't know she can be saved yet or not.

359
00:24:02,840 --> 00:24:04,320
So there's still hope for that,

360
00:24:04,430 --> 00:24:05,570
I'm not gonna give up.

361
00:24:06,660 --> 00:24:08,560
I'd never allow that to happen.

362
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:17,400
Hey, you.

